# LeDream Project Context

This is a fork of [huggingface/lerobot](https://github.com/huggingface/lerobot) for PCB placement robotics. The upstream remote is `upstream`.

Read `ledream_changelog.md` for full details on what files are custom vs modified from upstream.

## Key files

- `ledream_changelog.md` -- documents all fork changes and upstream sync instructions
- `configs/*.json` -- training configs (draccus/JSON format for `lerobot-train --config_path`)
- `Makefile` -- primary workflow interface (training, eval, recording, checkpoint management)

## Naming convention

HF model repos: `{dataset}_{policy}[-{variant}]-{checkpoint}`
- dataset: short alias (e.g. `pcb100x`, `pcb_v1`)
- policy: `act`, `dp`, `pi05`
- variant: optional (e.g. `novae`, `b32`)
- checkpoint: zero-padded step (e.g. `010000`)

Config filenames match the base name (without checkpoint), e.g. `configs/pcb100x_act.json`.

## Makefile workflow

- `make train CONFIG=... [OVERRIDES="..."]` -- run training locally
- `make train-cmd CONFIG=...` -- print command for Lightning AI job UI
- `make eval MODEL=dopaul/... [EPHEMERAL=true]` -- quick real-robot eval
- `make upload-latest JOB=...` -- upload checkpoint to HF
- `make list-jobs` / `make list-configs` / `make list-checkpoints JOB=...`

## When making changes

- Update `ledream_changelog.md` when adding, removing, or modifying files (especially upstream source)
- New training experiments should get a config file in `configs/`
- Use `hf` (not `huggingface-cli`) for HF CLI commands
- HF user is `dopaul`
